name: Ragnar Trail McDowell Mountain - AZ
intro:
Ragnar Trail McDowell Mountain – AZ, presented by Salomon, is the overnight desert trail running adventure that southwest runners cannot miss. Held in the McDowell Mountain Range, just northeast of Scottsdale, teams will conquer the course at McDowell Mountain Regional Park.

With over 50 miles of breathtakingly diverse trails, this area provides majestic mountain views, epic desert flora and fauna, and some seriously fun trails! Swooping descents, rocky climbs, and smooth star-lit, sandy washes await you and your team. You may even catch a glimpse of the elusive Javelina while you are serenaded by the songs of howling coyotes during your run. With one of the most transformative sunrises in the series, this course will not disappoint! Cool desert air at night, warm, clear sunny skies during the day, and miles of epic trail running are all part of the deal!

Ragnar Trail McDowell Mountain-AZ is part of the Double Medal Series. Double your bling by running Ragnar Trail McDowell Mountain-AZ in 2016 and Reebok Ragnar Del Sol in 2017 to earn yourself the Phoenix Double Medal. VOTE for you favorite medal design here!

village:
The Ragnar Village is the heart and soul of the event. Each trail begins and ends in Ragnar Village. It is the start line, the finish line, and the exchange point. After each loop you will return to the support of your teammates and the adulation of the teams around you. Ragnar Village will be complete with:

    • Bonfire

    • Food & snacks (Friday night pasta dinner included for each runner)

    • Freak Brothers Pizza available 24hrs

    • Movies

    • S’mores, Coffee, & Hot Cocoa                                                                      

    • Music

    • Billions of stars

Ragnar Village is located at the McDowell Mountain Regional Park: 16300 McDowell Mountain Park Dr, Fort McDowell, AZ 85264

 

Team Campsite

Each team will be given a location to set up their team campsite in the Ragnar Village. Camping is FREE to runners, family, friends, and crew on Thursday and Friday nights. For more information on your team’s campsite please see the Travel & Lodging page.

 

Schedule

The schedule will be posted closer to the race date. 

 

Partners

Salomon - Demo a pair of Salomon shoes out on a loop, free of charge of course!

REI - Learn how to make the perfect camp cup of coffee, lounge in the REI hammocks, or try night writing for the first time!

Nathan - Get your photo taken with the What Color is Your Pee Banner! Nathan products for purchase as well.

CEP Compression - Learn how compression socks will speed up your reovery by talking with Kendall in the Merchandise Tent

Nuun - Electrolyte samples to keep you hydrated throughout the weekend

Bondi Band - Stop by the Bondi Band booth to purchase your moisture wicking headbands, armbands, and other must have running accessories

Elevated Legs - Pneumatic compression leg sleeves will help with your recovery. Come get your legs squeezed at the Elevated Legs tent.

Freak Brothers Pizza - Freakishly good pizza served 24 hours a day to keep you fueled between your runs!

Goal Zero Charging Station - Solar Powered batteries to keep your electronics charged for the race weekend

Klymit - Borrow a Klymit mat for the weekend to get optimal sleep through the night!

Klean Kanteen - Water station and cold brew coffee!

Telic - Get your Ragnar branded recovery sandals in the Merchandise tent

The Tube Waistband - Wearable waistband to hold all your running essentials for sale!

BEX Sunglasses - High quality sunglasses that stay put as you exercise.

2Toms - Sport Shield anti chafe product to protect you from that dreaded chafe!

ClickCamp- Skip the packing stress. Come to Ragnar in a relaxed way, without your tent. A Click Camp tent, sleeping bag, air mattress, cot, and chairs are waiting for you. You just show up and focus on the important things: your team and the race.

charity:
McDowell Mountain is just around the corner. Make the weekend even more meaningful by fundraising for a Ragnar charity partner or your favorite charity on everydayhero, the official fundraising platform of Ragnar Relay Series! 

Simply go here (or click on the everydayhero logo above) and choose your favorite charity – it’s that easy!  Your fundraising page will be created and you can start making every step count.

To date, the Ragnar community has fundraised over 1 million dollars so let's keep it going! 

Questions? Email nonprofits@everydayhero.com.

McDowell Mountain Sororan Conservancy

Ragnar Trail McDowell Mountain-AZ has partnered with the McDowell Mountain Sonoran Conservancy who works with more than 500 volunteers to help protect and promote the McDowell Sonoran Preserve through trail building, guiding hikes, education and research, among other efforts.

legs.name: Green Loop - Shallmo Wash Trail
legs.description: Flat-ish, fast-ish, and super fun to run—who says it isn’t easy being green? Green loop starts off with the red loop, splitting off just short of a mile to take you along the lower scenic trail. The first half of this loop offers a climb so subtle, you’ll swear you’re on flat ground. After meeting up briefly with red again, green takes off down a brand new trail paralleling Shallmo Wash. Speedsters will have fun bombing down this loop, while the rest of us can sit back, relax, and enjoy the gentle rollers all the way back into the village.

legs.name: Yellow Loop - T-Bone Ridge
legs.description: This year, yellow starts off with a climb up T-Bone Ridge. Intense but short, the view from the top of the Ridge is your first reward; we recommend taking a second to take it all in. After a quick scramble down the back of the Ridge, you’re next rewarded with 2.5 miles of fantastic single-track trail. It’s just hard enough to keep your brain and feet will be happy. Your final reward? You’re almost done! For the last bit of the loop, you join up with red for a speedy finish back into the village.

legs.name: Red Loop - Pemberton Trail
legs.description: At 6.6 miles, Pemberton is the longest of the three trails. After splitting from green, red loop takes you on a single track climb through the saguaros to the summit of the Scenic Trail. It’s challenging, but that’s what makes it great! From the top, you’ll enjoy a gorgeous panoramic view of the mountains. After descending the Scenic Trail, you’ll converge on to the Pemberton Trail, briefly meeting up with green again. After green splits off to the left, you head straight ahead for the water station (it’s the only one on the loop, so fill up!). From there, you’ll continue down Pemberton, eventually leaving the trail to cut down a sandy wash. The wash is tough, and may feel longer than it is, but you’ll be back on trail before you know if, meeting up with yellow for a final push in to the village.

travel.content:
Team Campsite

Each team will have a location to set up their team campsite in the Ragnar Village. 

• Awards will be given for the best decorated team campsite and almost anything goes: tents, canopies, couches, camping chairs, BBQ's, kiddie pools full of Kool-Aid, whatever. No commercial tents will be allowed.

• Ragnar does not assign specific campsites but we do ask that your team take up less than 300 sq-ft.

• Camping in the Ragnar Village is FREE to runners, family, friends, and crew on Thursday and Friday nights.

• If you don't have all the camping gear, or don't want to worry about it.. check out Click Camp. They set up and clean up for you- all you need to bring are your running clothes and shoes! 

• Teams will be allowed in the venue on Thursday between 5:00 PM — 10:00 PM. No teams will not be allowed in the venue until 5:00 PM on Thursday.

• Race check-in opens on Friday morning. There is no Saturday night camping this year. Everyone must be out of the venue by 8:00 PM on Saturday night.

• Absolutely no dogs will be allowed on the course, campsite, or at the event. We love dogs but this is a safety issue for our participants and for the dogs.

• Check out the Trail Guide for a list of other things that are and are not allowed on the campsite.
 

Directions

Directions to McDowell Mountain Regional Park can be found HERE. Closest major airport is the Phoenix Sky Harbor International Airport (PHX). 


RV's

• No RV camping will be available. 
 

Click Camp

How it works- It's just like a hotel. All you have to do is reserve your tent, check-in with our on site hosts, and then check out. 

When you arrive on-site Click Camp will have a private area where you are greeted by one of our hosts. The hosts will quickly confirm your reservation then walk you to your tent accommodations. To make your return trip to your tent easier we have identified your tent with a small placard.

When you finish running your race make your way back to your tent and we will help you with check out when you're ready. 

With Click Camp there is no clean-up, no storing, no wondering where you'll sleep, and most importantly a good night's rest so you can run your best race. 

Elevated Legs Rental

Turn your campsite into a recovery station! Our partners Elevated Legs are renting legs for $120 for the whole race - that's $15/person for a team of 8! Don’t forget that you will need a power source. We highly recommend the Goal Zero Yetis.

For more information check out: http://elevatedlegs.com/rent/ragnar/

*Be sure to rent your legs before Monday, October 31st to ensure delivery before the race!*

Sustainability

Ragnar seeks ways to reduce the carbon footprint of our races. We ask that you join us in this effort by carpooling on your drive to the event and striving to bring only two vehicles per team.
